<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-295-359  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 295 359.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Jan 1989 v14 n1 p143(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hooked on Smalltalk-80 for the Mac. (Software Review) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Crabb, Don.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Smalltalk-80 2.3, from ParcPlace Systems, is a package that reallyexemplifies the practical power of object-oriented programming.andO;The system consists of two functional parts: a virtual image,containing the program's language, complier, run-time system,graphical system libraries, and a variety of program developmenttools; and a virtual machine that links the operating system andhardware of a particular computer to the virtual image.andP;  Thecomplete Smalltalk-80 2.3 system comes on six disks andincorporates a compiler, a symbolic debugger, object browsers,inspectors, the visual interface and full support for displayinginformation.andP;  The system costs $995 and requires a Mac Plus, SE orII with at least 2Mbytes of RAM and 10Mbytes of hard disk space.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   ParcPlace Systems Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Smalltalk-80 2.3 (Computer program language).andO;Topic:     EvaluationProgram Development ToolsSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>